The paper deals with the problem of learning mixtures of Gaussians, which is a common topic in machine learning and statistics. The use of PAC-style learning models and the method of moments suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and the development of sub-algorithms, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem of learning probability distributions could also be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
